### 4. KANO MODEL ANALYSIS

Must-Have Features (Basic Needs):
- [FEATURE]: Without it, product is unusable/uncompetitive
- [FEATURE]: Expected by all customers, no delight if present
- Action: Must include, but don't over-invest

Performance Features (Linear Value):
- [FEATURE]: More is better, directly increases satisfaction
- [FEATURE]: Customers can compare quantitatively
- Action: Competitive parity or advantage

Delighters (Excitement Features):
- [FEATURE]: Unexpected, creates wow moments
- [FEATURE]: Not missed if absent, loved if present
- Action: Source of differentiation

Indifferent Features:
- [FEATURE]: Customers don't care either way
- Action: Don't build

Reverse Features:
- [FEATURE]: Some customers want, others actively dislike
- Action: Make optional/configurable or skip

